      "span_text": "The integrin ligand intercellular adhesion molecule (icam)-1 and bystin-like (bysl), the mouse homologue of a human cytoplasmic component of a cell adhesion complex, are up-regulated. Furthermore, the proline±serine±threonine phosphatase-interacting protein 1 (pstpip1), also known as cd2bp1, is downregulated, leading to enhanced CD2-mediated adhesion [CITATION_1] ."
